  {
    q: 'Does the time of day affect the river flow?',
    a: '<p>The Sella flow is stable throughout the day — it is not a river with significant hourly variations, unlike Alpine rivers fed by snowmelt. What does change is the <strong>water temperature</strong> (a little warmer in mid-afternoon) and the <strong>light</strong>, which affects photos and the perceived temperature.</p>',
  },
